            "answer_text": "There is no way of knowing for sure what Freddie\u2019s private thoughts were when he wrote the song. No one but Freddie can tell us, and he is no longer around. It\u2019s important to remember that \u201cWho Wants to Live Forever\u201d was written for the movie The Highlander, which has themes related to immortality. Therefore, it\u2019s reasonable to assume the song was simply written for a film about immortality. At the same time, it\u2019s reasonable to believe that HIV/AIDS and his own mortality was at the very least at the back of his mind. I will never understand what it was like for a gay man in the 1980s. I can imagine the AIDS crisis was a nightmare. I wasn\u2019t around at the time, but can imagine HIV/AIDS was gaining widespread coverage in the media, and ingrained itself in the public\u2019s conscious. Maybe he did write the song on commission for the film, but maybe it\u2019s message had a strong, private meaning to him. Who knows? Edit: Freddie Mercury didn\u2019t write the song, Brian May did. I guess the answer is no, than! ",
