            "answer_text": "The song was written by Brian May for the soundtrack of the movie highlander. He wrote it in the backseat of the car after seeing the movie scene it was meant for. It is completely unrelated to the life and experiences of Freddie Mercury. No one can deny that Freddie's voice \u201cmade\u201d the song though. On the album recording May sings along with Mercury, but in live versions Freddie sang the song and just took it to another level. It brings me to tears when I listen to it, because Freddie gives the song so much meaning and feeling. It's one of my ultimate favorite songs ever. And no, Mercury only found out in 1987 that he was diagnosed with aids. However I do think he knew he wouldn't live long, not after seeing so many of his friends succumb to the illness. Queen - Who Want to Live Forever (live at Wembley) ",
