                "name": "Paul Duggan",
                "href": "/profile/Paul-Duggan-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "Good answer from Neil Anderson. It\u2019s worth remembering that Brian May wrote this for the soundtrack to the movie Highlander. The lyrics, while being general, are very much inspired by the themes in the film and I don\u2019t think Brian May would regard them as \u2018personal\u2019, much less Freddie. What I find more interesting is the writing and performance of a song like Was It All Worth It. The band would have been aware that Freddie was dying at this point. When this song was recorded they would have known that it was possible that The Miracle would be their last album and they placed it as the last song in the album. The same goes of course for The Show Must Go On (Brian and Freddie together), which I think is even more powerful and poignant. ",
