            "answer_text": "According to his partner Jim Hutton, Mercury was diagnosed with AIDS shortly after Easter of 1987. Up until November 23, 1991, Mercury denied rumours of being HIV positive and was stalked by photographers and paparazzi who pointed out his appearance and absence at performances. On November 24, 1991, 24 hours after his announcement to the world, Mercury died at the age of 45. The official cause of death was bronchial pneumonia resulting from AIDS. So, we\u2019ll never know if Freddie was aware at that time whether he was already ill or not. ",
